<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT AND MAIN BEARINGS (RECONDITIONING) - FLYWHEEL HOUSING
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>FLYWHEEL HOUSING</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the oil pan removed, remove the flywheel housing as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the six bolts and washers which support the housing. (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150729">7.29</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the housing from the crankcase.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The housing is supported by two alignment dowels.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the flywheel housing gasket and discard.</para>
                <figure id="ef4150728" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11604" filename="../figcg1/CG11604.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.28. Remove Oil Pan.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150729" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12172" filename="../figcg1/CG12172.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.29. Remove Flywheel Housing</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
